tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and mildly elevated LDL cholesterol, suggesting increased cardiovascular risk. All other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Renal function should be further evaluated and cardiovascular risk factors addressed.
